Don't get me wrong, I loved the first movie since I was a kid. It's a great adventurous family film that will never bore you. Very compelling, funny characters especially the character of Simon. Colin Firth does a superb job of portraying a struggling father raising seven children. Though I have to admit, this theme of hiring a nanny is sort of similar to theme of the film/musical Sound of Music. But either way, this first fim of Nanny McPhee is all five stars.
But the second one, was a bit of a disappointment. First, the cast changed as well as the time period. The acting in the second movie by the five children are just too predictable that it makes me cringe so much. I felt bored in the middle of the film and the ending was just expected from the beginning. Suggest you watch the first.

As far as the movie, they are both good movies; fun for kids and adults, in my experience.

As for the DVD/package itself, they are both on one DVD and there are no extras (at all). So, if you're someone who likes DVD extras, get the individual copies. Or if you do disc-to-digital conversions (like on VUDU, Flixster, etc.) with your DVDs, it only recognizes the disc as Nanny McPhee Returns (i.e., you can only "convert" that movie, not the original).
